{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1e5fb39b-0205-4465-a2da-744195dc05c8","content":"In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates a new instance **per HTTP request** — each request gets a fresh `DbContext`. In MAUI, there are no HTTP requests. The app is a single long-running process, so `AddScoped` effectively behaves like **`AddSingleton`**. Your `DbContext` is created once and reused forever, keeping its change tracker and cached entities across all navigations.\n\n**Fixes (pick one):**\n\n1. **Use `AddTransient`** — a new `DbContext` per injection:\n   ```csharp\n   builder.Services.AddTransient<MyDbContext>();\n   ```\n\n2. **Use a `DbContext` factory** (recommended):\n   ```csharp\n   builder.Services.AddDbContextFactory<MyDbContext>();\n   ```\n   Then inject `IDbContextFactory<MyDbContext>` and create short-lived contexts:\n   ```csharp\n   using var db = _factory.CreateDbContext();\n   var items = db.Items.ToList();\n   ```\n\nThe factory approach gives you explicit control over the `DbContext` lifetime and avoids issues with stale data, tracking conflicts, and memory growth.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"95f7a698-413a-4e5f-8e5e-d88eefacbf7e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a common pitfall when moving from ASP.NET Core to .NET MAUI regarding dependency injection scoping, specifically with `AddScoped` and `DbContext`. This is a conceptual question — no code to look at, no repo to explore. I can answer directly.\n\nThe key issue: In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates a new instance per HTTP request. In MAUI, there's no concept of an \"HTTP request\" — the app is a single long-running process. So `AddScoped` in MAUI effectively behaves like `AddSingleton`, meaning the same DbContext instance is reused across the entire app lifetime, causing stale/cached data to persist across navigations.","outputTokens":456,"requestId":"1017:92DE6:162623F:18D0D20:69FD3688"},"id":"9d756a72-7408-4332-9cf4-8261244c164b","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:04:20.520Z","parentId":"274f1a9c-1814-47c9-a416-8ecb6227ae9c"}
